 level cap so I can spec more in enhancement, or they make a class change. I want the 48s, I think, so I can do well in RvR, and I want 24r so my heals aren't miserable. I might go for a more balanced template, like 40s/26r/24e, but more than likely will stick with what I've got. I'm more of the offensive type of person anyway.<br><br>I realize that my group role in PvE and even in RvR is partly to heal and rez people. I can fulfill both with the template I've got, although not as well as a rejuv cleric, and I won't have much in the way of buffs. However, I'll have a lot of offensive capability and will be a great design for keep defense. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub32.ezboard.com/bwarandretribution.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=harleq>Harleq</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFF00>(3/24/02 8:59:48 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub32.ezboard.com/fwarandretributionfrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=32.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.geocities.com/harleq01/Pic.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 48s/24r/6e..</span><hr size=1> &lt;Alamais&gt; Personally that new rez isnt really worth it, you still got rez sickness, least thats my opinion, go for that last nuke.<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> Meresin</span><br> <span class=usertitle>Unregistered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFF00>(3/28/02 7:39:20 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub32.ezboard.com/fwarandretributionfrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=32.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Hm.</span><hr size=1> Hm..Been really thinking about changing my ultimate goal permanently. I think 40s/25r/26e would be good. 25r gets two pretty good heals, and 26e would give me plenty of buffs to work with. I think you're right about the rez though. If I go with 48s, it'll be with more enh and less rejuv than I originally planned. Besides..Clerics aren't offensive casters. Their spells don't have range, and for good reason..They're more laid out so they can defend themselves. Standard heals are good, but I'm wondering about 48 smite or 40 smite. How much of a damage hit would I take if I went with the lower smite? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub32.ezboard.com/uclericlochness.showPublicProfile?language=EN>cleric lochness</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Warlord</span><br> <font color=#FFFF00>(4/1/02 9:00:29 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub32.ezboard.com/fwarandretributionfrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=32.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Hm.</span><hr size=1> I was on the track for the 48 smite, but decided to go higher in enhancement.  I figured ion the l,ong run being able to buff my party would provide more overall power.<br><br>Course I been 42 for 2 months but plan to level to 43 this month if I can find people to hunt some fun camps and get away from the bolring trees and goblins <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> Meresin</span><br> <span class=usertitle>Unregistered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFF00>(5/1/02 4:05:20 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub32.ezboard.com/fwarandretributionfrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=32.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> ;&gt;</span><hr size=1> I changed my mind on it too and I'm going 40s/26e/25r. Seems a good idea..But everything seems like a good idea at the time. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub32.ezboard.com/uranorolan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>RANOROLAN</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFF00>(5/24/02 11:59:31 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub32.ezboard.com/fwarandretributionfrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=32.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ;&gt;</span><hr size=1> Depends what you want to do really.<br><br>I am sticking to 45 or 46 rejuv (when i can respec) as i like being a support person in the group. However the high smite does mean you will hit hard (although remember that spirit resists tend to be high on mid/hib characters) and have a decent length mez.<br><br>My current spec is 45 rejuv, 27 smite and 13 enhance, although when i can repsec i will drop most of the smite and put the points into enhance<br><br>But it really depends what role you want to play, a smite cleric is the frontline character, a rejuv/enhance heavy cleric tends to drop back behind the group.<br><br>Rano <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub32.ezboard.com/fwarandretributionfrm9.showPrevMessage?topicID=32.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub32.ezboard.com/fwarandretributionfrm9.showNextMessage?topicID=32.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub32.ezboard.com/fwarandretributionfrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=32.topic&index=5><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/slate/addReply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub32.ezboard.com/fwarandretributionfrm9.emailToFriend?topicID=32.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com